<task id="task_turkish_salad_recipe">
    <title>Turkish Salad Recipe</title>
    <shortdesc>This refreshing and savory Middle Eastern salad is perfect for a summer lunch or dinner side dish.</shortdesc>
    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p>You will need:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><p><b>Supplies</b></p></li>
                <li><p>Cutting board</p></li>
                <li><p>Large, sharp chefâ€™s knife</p></li>
                <li><p>Large mixing bowl</p></li>
                <li><p>Serving spoon</p></li>
            </ul>
            <ul>
                <li><p><b>Ingredients</b></p></li>
                <li><p>2 medium cucumbers</p></li>
                <li><p>3 medium tomatoes</p></li>
                <li><p>1/2 small head of cabbage</p></li>
                <li><p>1 bunch fresh curly parsley</p></li>
                <li><p>10 peppermint leaves</p></li>
                <li><p>1 tsp. salt</p></li>
                <li><p>1/2 tsp. pepper</p></li>
                <li><p>2 Tbsp. extra virgin olive oil</p></li>
                <li><p>1-2 Tbsp. lemon juice</p></li>
            </ul>
        </context>
        <steps>
            <step>
                <cmd>Peel cucumbers and cut off ends. Cut tomatoes, cucumbers, and cabbage in a rough chop and add to bowl.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Chop parsley and peppermint finely and add to bowl.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Add salt and pepper and stir all thoroughly.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Drizzle olive oil and lemon juice over salad just before serving and stir to coat vegetables.</cmd>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Serve chilled.</cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
</task>
